    {
      "type": 1,
      "content": {
        "json": "# \ud83d\uddc4\ufe0f Azure SQL Monitoring Dashboard\n**Metrics-only \u00b7 Free tier \u00b7 No Log Analytics required**\n\n---"
      },
      "name": "title"
    },
    {
      "type": 1,
      "content": {
        "json": "## \ud83d\udea8 Subscription Health Overview\n> Subscriptions shown here have **unhealthy resources** or **fired metric alerts**. Green = nothing to check.\n\n---"
      },
      "name": "overview-header"
    },
    {
      "type": 3,
      "content": {
        "version": "KqlItem/1.0",
        "query": "HealthResources\n| where type =~ 'microsoft.resourcehealth/availabilitystatuses'\n| where id has 'microsoft.sql' or id has 'sqlvirtualmachines'\n| extend State = tostring(properties.availabilityState)\n| extend ResourceName = tostring(split(id, '/')[-1])\n| join kind=leftouter (\n    ResourceContainers\n    | where type == 'microsoft.resources/subscriptions'\n    | project subscriptionId, SubscriptionName = name\n  ) on subscriptionId\n| summarize\n    Total      = count(),\n    Unavailable = countif(State =~ 'Unavailable'),\n    Degraded    = countif(State =~ 'Degraded'),\n    Available   = countif(State =~ 'Available')\n    by SubscriptionName\n| where Unavailable > 0 or Degraded > 0\n| order by Unavailable desc, Degraded desc",
        "size": 1,
        "title": "\u26a0\ufe0f Resource Health Issues by Subscription",
        "noDataMessage": "\u2705 No health issues found \u2014 or Microsoft.ResourceHealth provider not yet registered. Run the registration PowerShell script to enable this.",
        "noDataMessageStyle": 3,
        "queryType": 1,
        "resourceType": "microsoft.resourcegraph/resources",
        "crossComponentResources": [
          "{Subscription}"
        ],
        "visualization": "table",
        "gridSettings": {
          "formatters": [
            {
              "columnMatch": "IssueCount",
              "formatter": 18,
              "formatOptions": {
                "thresholdsOptions": "icons",
                "thresholdsGrid": [
                  {
                    "operator": ">",
                    "thresholdValue": "0",
                    "representation": "failed",
                    "text": "{0}"
                  },
                  {
                    "operator": "Default",
                    "thresholdValue": null,
                    "representation": "success",
                    "text": "{0}"
                  }
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "filter": true,
          "sortBy": [
            {
              "itemKey": "IssueCount",
              "sortOrder": 2
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "customWidth": "50",
      "name": "overview-health-by-sub"
    },
    {
      "type": 3,
      "content": {
        "version": "KqlItem/1.0",
        "query": "AlertsManagementResources\n| where type =~ 'microsoft.alertsmanagement/alerts'\n| where tostring(properties.essentials.monitorCondition) =~ 'Fired'\n| where tostring(properties.essentials.targetResourceType) in~ (\n    'microsoft.sql/servers/databases',\n    'microsoft.sql/managedinstances',\n    'microsoft.compute/virtualmachines'\n  )\n| extend\n    AlertName    = tostring(properties.essentials.alertRule),\n    Severity     = tostring(properties.essentials.severity),\n    ResourceName = tostring(properties.essentials.targetResourceName),\n    FiredAt      = todatetime(properties.essentials.startDateTime)\n| join kind=leftouter (\n    ResourceContainers\n    | where type == 'microsoft.resources/subscriptions'\n    | project subscriptionId, SubscriptionName = name\n  ) on subscriptionId\n| summarize\n    FiredAlerts = count(),\n    Severities  = strcat_array(make_set(Severity), ', '),\n    AlertNames  = strcat_array(make_set(AlertName), ', '),\n    OldestFired = min(FiredAt)\n    by SubscriptionName\n| order by FiredAlerts desc",
        "size": 1,
        "title": "\ud83d\udd14 Fired Metric Alerts by Subscription",
        "noDataMessage": "\u2705 No fired alerts \u2014 either all clear, or no metric alerts have been configured yet.",
        "noDataMessageStyle": 3,
        "queryType": 1,
        "resourceType": "microsoft.resourcegraph/resources",
        "crossComponentResources": [
          "{Subscription}"
        ],
        "visualization": "table",
        "gridSettings": {
          "formatters": [
            {
              "columnMatch": "FiredAlerts",
              "formatter": 18,
              "formatOptions": {
                "thresholdsOptions": "icons",
                "thresholdsGrid": [
                  {
                    "operator": ">",
                    "thresholdValue": "0",
                    "representation": "failed",
                    "text": "{0}"
                  },
                  {
                    "operator": "Default",
                    "thresholdValue": null,
                    "representation": "success",
                    "text": "{0}"
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "columnMatch": "Severities",
              "formatter": 1
            }
          ],
          "filter": true,
          "sortBy": [
            {
              "itemKey": "FiredAlerts",
              "sortOrder": 2
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "customWidth": "50",
      "name": "overview-alerts-by-sub"
    },
    {
      "type": 3,
      "content": {
        "version": "KqlItem/1.0",
        "query": "Resources\n| where type in~ ('microsoft.sql/servers/databases','microsoft.sql/managedinstances','microsoft.sqlvirtualmachine/sqlvirtualmachines')\n| where not (type =~ 'microsoft.sql/servers/databases' and name == 'master')\n| join kind=leftouter (\n    ResourceContainers\n    | where type == 'microsoft.resources/subscriptions'\n    | project subscriptionId, SubscriptionName = name\n  ) on subscriptionId\n| summarize\n    SQLDatabases     = countif(type =~ 'microsoft.sql/servers/databases'),\n    ManagedInstances = countif(type =~ 'microsoft.sql/managedinstances'),\n    SQLVMs           = countif(type =~ 'microsoft.sqlvirtualmachine/sqlvirtualmachines')\n    by SubscriptionName\n| order by SubscriptionName asc",
        "size": 1,
        "title": "\ud83d\udccb SQL Resources per Subscription",
        "noDataMessage": "No SQL resources found in selected subscriptions.",
        "noDataMessageStyle": 2,
        "queryType": 1,
        "resourceType": "microsoft.resourcegraph/resources",
        "crossComponentResources": [
          "{Subscription}"
        ],
        "visualization": "table",
        "gridSettings": {
          "filter": true
        }
      },
      "customWidth": "50",
      "name": "overview-allclear"
    },
    {
      "type": 1,
      "content": {
        "json": "> \ud83d\udca1 **Note on storage % alerts:** The '\ud83d\udd14 Fired Alerts' panel above only shows issues if you have **metric alerts configured**. Without them, storage/CPU thresholds won't appear here. See the per-resource sections below for raw metric charts, or ask for a PowerShell script to bulk-create free metric alerts (storage >85%, CPU >90%) across all your databases.\n\n---"
      },
      "name": "overview-note"
    },
    {
      "type": 3,
      "content": {
        "version": "KqlItem/1.0",
        "query": "Resources\n| where type in~ ('microsoft.sql/servers/databases', 'microsoft.sql/managedinstances', 'microsoft.sqlvirtualmachine/sqlvirtualmachines')\n| where not (type =~ 'microsoft.sql/servers/databases' and name == 'master')\n| summarize Count = count() by ResourceType = case(\n    type =~ 'microsoft.sql/servers/databases', '\ud83d\uddc4\ufe0f SQL Databases',\n    type =~ 'microsoft.sql/managedinstances', '\ud83c\udfe2 Managed Instances',\n    '\ud83d\udda5\ufe0f SQL VMs'\n  )\n| order by ResourceType asc",
        "size": 4,
        "title": "Resource Inventory",
        "queryType": 1,
        "resourceType": "microsoft.resourcegraph/resources",
        "crossComponentResources": [
          "{Subscription}"
        ],
        "visualization": "tiles",
        "tileSettings": {
          "showBorder": true,
          "titleContent": {
            "columnMatch": "ResourceType",
            "formatter": 1
          },
          "leftContent": {
            "columnMatch": "Count",
            "formatter": 12,
            "formatOptions": {
              "palette": "blue"
            }
          }
        }
      },
      "name": "inventory-tiles"
    },
    {
      "type": 3,
      "content": {
        "version": "KqlItem/1.0",
        "query": "HealthResources\n| where type =~ 'microsoft.resourcehealth/availabilitystatuses'\n| where id has '/microsoft.sql/' or id has '/sqlvirtualmachines/'\n| extend ResourceName = tostring(split(id, '/')[-1])\n| extend State = tostring(properties.availabilityState)\n| extend Summary = tostring(properties.summary)\n| extend ResourceGroup = tostring(resourceGroup)\n| join kind=leftouter (\n    ResourceContainers\n    | where type == 'microsoft.resources/subscriptions'\n    | project subscriptionId, SubscriptionName = name\n  ) on subscriptionId\n| project ResourceName, SubscriptionName, ResourceGroup, State, Summary\n| order by State asc, SubscriptionName asc, ResourceName asc",
        "size": 1,
        "title": "\ud83c\udfe5 Resource Health \u2014 All SQL Resources",
        "queryType": 1,
        "resourceType": "microsoft.resourcegraph/resources",
        "crossComponentResources": [
          "{Subscription}"
        ],
        "visualization": "table",
        "gridSettings": {
          "formatters": [
            {
              "columnMatch": "State",
              "formatter": 18,
              "formatOptions": {
                "thresholdsOptions": "icons",
                "thresholdsGrid": [
                  {
                    "operator": "==",
                    "thresholdValue": "Available",
                    "representation": "success",
                    "text": "{0}{1}"
                  },
                  {
                    "operator": "==",
                    "thresholdValue": "Degraded",
                    "representation": "warning",
                    "text": "{0}{1}"
                  },
                  {
                    "operator": "==",
                    "thresholdValue": "Unavailable",
                    "representation": "failed",
                    "text": "{0}{1}"
                  },
                  {
                    "operator": "Default",
                    "thresholdValue": null,
                    "representation": "unknown",
                    "text": "{0}{1}"
                  }
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "filter": true,
          "sortBy": [
            {
              "itemKey": "State",
              "sortOrder": 2
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "name": "resource-health"
    },
    {
      "type": 3,
      "content": {
        "version": "KqlItem/1.0",
        "query": "Resources\n| where type in~ ('microsoft.sql/servers/databases', 'microsoft.sql/managedinstances', 'microsoft.sqlvirtualmachine/sqlvirtualmachines')\n| where not (type =~ 'microsoft.sql/servers/databases' and name == 'master')\n| extend ResourceType = case(\n    type =~ 'microsoft.sql/servers/databases', 'SQL Database',\n    type =~ 'microsoft.sql/managedinstances', 'Managed Instance',\n    'SQL VM'\n  )\n| extend Tier = coalesce(tostring(sku.tier), tostring(sku.name), '-')\n| extend Capacity = tostring(sku.capacity)\n| extend Location = tostring(location)\n| join kind=leftouter (\n    ResourceContainers\n    | where type == 'microsoft.resources/subscriptions'\n    | project subscriptionId, SubscriptionName = name\n  ) on subscriptionId\n| project ResourceType, name, SubscriptionName, resourceGroup, Location, Tier, Capacity, id\n| order by SubscriptionName asc, ResourceType asc, name asc",
        "size": 1,
        "title": "\ud83d\udccb All SQL Resources",
        "queryType": 1,
        "resourceType": "microsoft.resourcegraph/resources",
        "crossComponentResources": [
          "{Subscription}"
        ],
        "visualization": "table",
        "gridSettings": {
          "formatters": [
            {
              "columnMatch": "name",
              "formatter": 13,
              "formatOptions": {
                "linkTarget": "Resource",
                "linkIsContextBlade": true
              }
            },
            {
              "columnMatch": "ResourceType",
              "formatter": 1
            }
          ],
          "filter": true,
          "sortBy": [
            {
              "itemKey": "ResourceType",
              "sortOrder": 1
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "name": "inventory-table"
    },
    {
      "type": 1,
      "content": {
        "json": "---\n## \ud83d\uddc4\ufe0f SQL Databases\n---"
      },
      "name": "sqldb-header"
    },
    {
      "type": 3,
      "content": {
        "version": "KqlItem/1.0",
        "query": "\nResources\n| where type =~ 'microsoft.sql/servers/databases'\n| where name != 'master'\n| join kind=leftouter (\n    ResourceContainers\n    | where type == 'microsoft.resources/subscriptions'\n    | project subscriptionId, SubscriptionName = name\n  ) on subscriptionId\n| extend\n    Server        = tostring(split(id, '/')[8]),\n    Tier          = tostring(sku.tier),\n    Capacity      = tostring(sku.capacity),\n    AllocatedGB   = round(todouble(properties.maxSizeBytes) / 1073741824, 1),\n    Edition       = tostring(sku.name),\n    Status        = tostring(properties.status)\n| project\n    ['Database']     = name,\n    SubscriptionName,\n    Server,\n    ['Resource Group'] = resourceGroup,\n    Tier,\n    Edition,\n    Capacity,\n    ['Allocated GB'] = AllocatedGB,\n    Status,\n    id\n| order by ['Allocated GB'] desc\n",
        "size": 1,
        "title": "\ud83d\udccb All Databases \u2014 sorted by allocated size (click name \u2192 Metrics blade)",
        "noDataMessage": "No data found.",
        "queryType": 1,
        "resourceType": "microsoft.resourcegraph/resources",
        "crossComponentResources": [
          "{Subscription}"
        ],
        "visualization": "table",
        "gridSettings": {
          "formatters": [
            {
              "columnMatch": "Database",
              "formatter": 13,
              "formatOptions": {
                "linkTarget": "Resource",
                "linkIsContextBlade": true
              }
            },
            {
              "columnMatch": "Status",
              "formatter": 18,
              "formatOptions": {
                "thresholdsOptions": "icons",
                "thresholdsGrid": [
                  {
                    "operator": "==",
                    "thresholdValue": "Online",
                    "representation": "success",
                    "text": "{0}"
                  },
                  {
                    "operator": "==",
                    "thresholdValue": "Paused",
                    "representation": "unknown",
                    "text": "{0}"
                  },
                  {
                    "operator": "Default",
                    "thresholdValue": null,
                    "representation": "failed",
                    "text": "{0}"
                  }
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "columnMatch": "id",
              "formatter": 5
            }
          ],
          "filter": true
        }
      },
      "customWidth": "100",
      "name": "sqldb-inv-grid"
    },
    {
      "type": 1,
      "content": {
        "json": "> \ud83d\udcc8 Charts below show **all selected databases** as individual lines. Red line = 90% threshold, yellow = 80%. Hover a line to identify the database. **Click any database name in the table above** to open its Metrics blade in the portal.\n"
